reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice but small
reviews.reviewText: As mentioned by other reviewers, this is a very small dish drain - I have a large kitchen sink and I thought it would fit from side to side when it was fully extended, but it doesn’t - it has two small rubber type holders to help it stay in place, but even those didn’t keep it from slipping off the edges of my large sinkIt does, however, fit my much smaller laundry room sink, as shown - it is very sturdy for what it is, and it is easily rinsed off and through when things are in it - I am hoping that the metal does not rust after a time, so that will remain to be seen - I do like that I can lift it out of the sink with items in it, and set it aside while I use the sink for something else - makes it easier to use a small sinkAll in all, would recommend this dish drain, just realize that it is very small

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Not only can this be an in-sink drying rack, but it could also be used as a large-spaced colander to clean larger vegetables—the silicone tabs to help it adhere to the counter are great. Good quality product. My only complaint is having to use Goo Gone to get the sticky residue from the tape holding the tag onto it. The rack is sturdy and good stainless steel quality.
